      "description": "ou are filling in a screen for the lqc-fe-ai-dev pipeline. Generate the React component file src/features/Portfolio/PortfolioLoanDetails/PortfolioLoanDetails.tsx. The same component renders in two targets without code changes:\n\nBrowser SPA — mounted at /portfolio/portfolio-loan-details inside AppShell.tsx (which provides nav, auth, theming).\nMCP widget — mounted inside a Claude.ai iframe via mcp-entry.generated.tsx with AppShell.mcp.tsx (no chrome). The build pipeline swaps AppShell and endpoint.generated.ts automatically; the screen file is target-agnostic.\nInputs you may read (zero-scan rule — nothing else):\n\nTODO_CONTEXT.generated.md in this folder\n.claude/skills/fe-dev/design-system-catalog.yaml\n.claude/skills/fe-dev/widget-catalog.yaml\n.claude/skills/fe-dev/slice-hints.yaml\nSibling generated files in this folder: types.generated.ts, fields.generated.tsx (detailRows), endpoint.generated.ts (usePortfolioLoanDetails() hook), route.generated.ts, i18n.generated.ts\nComponent contract:\n\nDefault export PortfolioLoanDetailsScreen — a function component, no props.\nCall the generated hook to fetch the readmodel; render Loading / ErrorState / EmptyState from @lqc/ui-kit for non-success states.\nOn success, render the page header (title + subtitle + Refresh/Edit actions) followed by sectioned DataRows cards composed via #lib/widgets (SectionedDetailRows) — no hand-rolled atom loops.\nSections (use SectionedDetailRows):\n\nIdentity — portfolioid · loanid · borrowername · acquisitiondate · maturitydate\nFinancial terms — loanamount · interestrate · capitalrequirement · expectedloss\nRisk profile — creditrating (pill) · riskband (pill) · probabilityofdefault (with inline progress) · simulateddefaultrate\nStress scenarios — expectedportfolioloss · tailriskloss · worstcaseloss (tint last row with error variant)\nRisk narrative — full-width card with the risknarrative field as a paragraph block\nLayout:\n\nSections 1–4 in a 2-column grid at ≥900px viewport, collapse to 1-column below 900px (MCP widgets render at ~600–800px). Use @lqc/ui-kit's Grid or Tailwind grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 — no custom breakpoints.\nSection 5 spans full width.\nFormatting: use formatCurrency / formatPercent / formatDate from #lib/widgets. Don't hand-roll formatters. For credit rating + risk band pills use the kit's Badge / Tag family per the design-system catalog.\n\ni18n: all visible strings (page title, section headers, button labels, error/empty copy) go through t(...) using the generated PortfolioLoanDetailsI18nKeys. No hardcoded English.\n\n",
